<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880603-0026 </DOCNO><HL> Big Board Picks Horowitz To Head Futures Exchange </HL><SO> </SO><IN> SCR STK CMD </IN><DATELINE> NEW YORK  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Lewis J. Horowitz was named chairman of the New York Stock Exchange's New York Futures Exchange and executive vice president of derivative products for the Big Board.    Mr. Horowitz, 53 years old, remains chief executive of the Futures Exchange and relinquishes the president's post, which won't be filled. The chairmanship has been expanded to a full-time position. Michael Creem, who retired from the futures exchange's board, had held the chairmanship as a director.    The Big Board also affirmed the election of Richard A. Grasso, 41, as president, chief operating officer and a board member. His nomination had been announced earlier this year.    Also, Stephen J. Paradise, 55, was named senior vice president of congressional and regulatory relations for the Big Board. He has been a Big Board vice president of government relations. Santo A. Famularo, 42, was named vice president of floor operations support for the futures exchange. He had been assistant vice president for market surveillance for the New York Stock Exchange.    The Big Board also elected three new directors to its board: John S. Chalsty, president and chief executive officer of Donaldson, Lufkin andamp; Jenrette Inc.; Rand V. Araskog, chairman and chief executive officer of ITT Corp.; and Martha T. Muse, chairman and president of the Tinker Foundation Inc. </TEXT></DOC>